-- Macquarie Receives Approval to Set up Non-Banking Finance Company in India
-- B y   R u t h   D a v i d
-- 2010-10-26T06:13:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/macquarie-india-wins-approval-for-non-banking-finance-update1-.html
Macquarie Group Ltd.  said it got
regulatory approval for a non-banking finance unit in India as
it seeks to join  Citigroup Inc.  and  Deutsche Bank AG  in
expanding operations in Asia’s second-fastest growing economy.  The NBFC registration will let Macquarie Finance (India)
Pvt. offer leasing, corporate and consumer financing, the
Sydney-based bank said in an e-mailed statement today. The unit
will start operations in December.  Macquarie Finance will help provide the  bank ’s Indian
clients, including companies and high-net worth individuals,
with margin funding, acquisition finance, bridge loans, loan
syndication, project and infrastructure finance and funding,
Fitch Ratings said in a separate statement. Macquarie has
invested $15 million in the business, it said.  Macquarie’s existing businesses in India include corporate
finance and advisory, infrastructure funds management, cash
equities sales and research and private wealth management, the
bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
